---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import HeroBackground from "../components/HeroBackground.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About — CompTech"
  description="One of Bangladesh's leading technology solution providers since 1989 — cloud, security, AI, data, and platform engineering for banks, government, and global development organisations."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <HeroBackground variant="waves" />
    <div class="container">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Cloud-driven change, since 1989.</h1>
      <p class="hero-lede">
        CompTech is one of Bangladesh&rsquo;s most established technology solution providers
        &mdash; designing, deploying, and operating the cloud, security, AI, and data
        platforms behind regulated workloads at banks, government agencies, and global
        development organisations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="prose">
        <h2>Three decades. One operating discipline.</h2>
        <p>
          Founded in Dhaka in <strong>1989</strong>, CompTech has grown into one of South
          Asia&rsquo;s most experienced systems integrators. We&rsquo;ve delivered more than
          <strong>200 projects</strong> across <strong>10+ industries</strong> with a
          <strong>70% repeat-client rate</strong> — a number that, more than any other,
          reflects what we care about. In <strong>2022</strong>, CompTech joined
          <strong>Pinaki Group</strong> to expand capability in cloud technology and
          cybersecurity for the next decade.
        </p>

        <h2>What we do</h2>
        <p>
          We deliver four practice areas end-to-end &mdash; <strong>cloud platforms</strong>,
          <strong>application modernization</strong>, <strong>end-to-end security</strong>,
          and <strong>operations &amp; managed services</strong> &mdash; with dedicated
          practice areas for <a href="/security/">security</a>, <a href="/ai/">AI</a>, and
          <a href="/data/">data &amp; analytics</a>. We engage where regulation, audit, and
          platform discipline define the shape of the engagement &mdash; <strong>banking and
          financial services</strong>, <strong>insurance</strong>, <strong>healthcare</strong>,
          <strong>telecom</strong>, <strong>manufacturing</strong>, <strong>energy</strong>,
          <strong>public sector</strong>, <strong>development and humanitarian</strong>, and
          <strong>defense and national security</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2>Mission &amp; vision</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Mission.</strong> Enable customers through every phase of their cloud
            journey while creating an empowering workplace for our team.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Vision.</strong> Be the independent go-to cloud partner for customers,
            skilled employees, and hyperscalers.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we deliver</h2>
        <p>
          Every engagement runs through the same five-phase discipline &mdash;
          <em>assess, design, deploy, operate, hand over</em> &mdash; sized to scope. We do
          not run open-ended retainers. The endpoint is a platform your team owns, with
          documentation deep enough to outlast staff turnover and a residual-risk register
          your audit function can sign for. See <a href="/methodology/">our methodology</a>
          for the full delivery model.
        </p>

        <h2>What you keep after we leave</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>A reference architecture</strong> specific to your environment, with
            architecture decisions (ADRs) for every non-obvious choice and the trade-offs
            considered for each.</li>
          <li><strong>A runbook set</strong> indexed by failure mode &mdash; not a generic
            wiki, but procedures verified against the system as it actually runs.</li>
          <li><strong>An operating model</strong> your platform team can sign for &mdash; on-call
            structure, escalation paths, alert hygiene, postmortem culture.</li>
          <li><strong>A residual-risk register</strong> &mdash; what we hardened, what we left in
            place by design, and what your operations team should watch for in the next 12
            months.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What we believe</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Customer outcomes first.</strong> We care deeply about the outcomes our
            clients are trying to achieve and support them with responsive, high-accountability
            delivery.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>GitOps-shaped from day one.</strong> Desired state in Git, reconciliation
            in the cluster, drift treated as a defect &mdash; never an out-of-band patch.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Identity is platform.</strong> Identity is not an application your team
            integrates with &mdash; it is the boundary your platform is shaped around.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Security is engineering work.</strong> Shift-left in the pipeline,
            shift-right at runtime, evidence at the source. Not a quarterly slide.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Documentation is a primary deliverable.</strong> The handover document is
            the engineering work, not a closeout task.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Our team</h2>
        <p>
          We are a team of <strong>150+ engineers, architects, and specialists</strong>, with
          <strong>50+ multi-cloud certified engineers</strong> across AWS, Microsoft Azure,
          Google Cloud, Oracle, Red Hat, NVIDIA, Cisco, and the wider Carbon-aligned stack.
          Every engagement is led by a named principal who stays accountable from scoping
          through handover.
        </p>

        <h2>Where we operate</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Corporate office.</strong> Richmond Concord, Level 7, 68 Gulshan Avenue,
          Dhaka 1212, Bangladesh.<br/>
          <strong>Head office.</strong> Pinaki Group, 29 Gareb-Newaz Avenue, Sector 11,
          Uttara, Dhaka 1230, Bangladesh.<br/>
          <strong>Delivery.</strong> Pan-South-Asia for regional engagements; remote-and-on-site
          for international development partners.
        </p>

        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
        <p>
          Engagements start with a short note describing what you&rsquo;re building. We
          reply with a concrete first-two-weeks scope and a definition of done.
          <a href="/contact/">Send us a note &rarr;</a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
